---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description =
  'How The Ledger decides what to publish — the position, the desks, the method, and how corrections work.';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="The Ledger — Editorial Framework"
  description={description}
  trimLeft="Editorial framework"
  trimRight="How The Ledger Works · MMXXVI"
>

  <section class="doc-title" aria-label="Editorial Framework">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow doc-title__eyebrow">How The Ledger Works</p>
      <h1 class="doc-title__title">Editorial<br /><em>Framework</em></h1>
      <p class="doc-title__subtitle">
        How The Ledger decides what to publish — the position, the desks, the method, and how corrections work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="doc">
    <div class="doc__inner">

      <aside class="doc-toc" aria-label="Contents">
        <p class="eyebrow doc-toc__label">Contents</p>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#position"><span class="doc-toc__numeral">I.</span><span>The position</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#standards"><span class="doc-toc__numeral">II.</span><span>Editorial standards</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#desks"><span class="doc-toc__numeral">III.</span><span>The desks</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#paper-trail"><span class="doc-toc__numeral">IV.</span><span>Paper Trail</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#independence"><span class="doc-toc__numeral">V.</span><span>Editorial independence</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#corrections"><span class="doc-toc__numeral">VI.</span><span>Corrections and retractions</span></a></li>
        </ol>
      </aside>

      <article class="doc-content">

        <section class="doc-section" id="position">
          <p class="doc-section__numeral">I.</p>
          <h1>The position</h1>
          <p>The Ledger is a decision-quality publication. Its purpose is to help readers see what a choice really costs — the trade-offs, hidden costs, limits, and real-world consequences that rankings, reviews, and quick answers tend to skip.</p>
          <p>The Ledger does not rank, sell, or publish buyer-style recommendations. It does not tell readers what to buy, hire, or believe. It helps them understand what they gain, what they give up, and what tends to happen over time.</p>
          <blockquote>The Ledger helps people see what a choice really costs after the easy answer stops working.</blockquote>
          <p>That line is the spine. If a piece does not help a reader do that, it is not a Ledger piece.</p>
          <p>The Ledger is not a blog, a content channel, or a marketing surface. It is a slow, deliberate publication that exists for readers who are tired of confident answers with no consequences.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="standards">
          <p class="doc-section__numeral">II.</p>
          <h1>Editorial standards</h1>

          <aside class="doc-filter" aria-label="Editorial filter">
            <p class="doc-filter__intro">A piece belongs in The Ledger if it can answer yes to both:</p>
            <p class="doc-filter__question"><em>Does it help a reader understand a choice, claim, system, or trade-off more clearly?</em></p>
            <p class="doc-filter__question"><em>Can it fairly explain the conditions where the easier, cheaper, faster, or more convenient answer is good enough — and where it stops working?</em></p>
            <p class="doc-filter__close">If the answer to either is no, the piece does not belong here.</p>
          </aside>

          <h3>What does not get published</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>"Top 10" or "Best of" rankings</li>
            <li>Affiliate-style reviews</li>
            <li>Marketing content dressed as editorial</li>
            <li>Hot takes and personality content</li>
            <li>Step-by-step how-to guides — execution belongs elsewhere</li>
            <li>Pieces published only to maintain a calendar</li>
            <li>Pieces that need the cheap option, the DIY route, or the no-service-needed answer to be wrong</li>
            <li>Pieces that exist mainly to justify a purchase, a vendor, or a side</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Silence is acceptable. Forced content is not.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="desks">
          <p class="doc-section__numeral">III.</p>
          <h1>The desks</h1>
          <p>The Ledger is organised into four desks. One is anchored to a domain. Three are anchored to ways of thinking. The mix is intentional. The Ledger does not pretend everything fits the same category type.</p>

          <h2>Home &amp; Services</h2>
          <p class="doc-meta">The domain desk</p>
          <p>Home &amp; Services is the only domain-based desk. It exists because home, property, and service decisions involve real money, real consequences, and the kind of conflicting claims that benefit from honest explanation.</p>
          <p>Use this desk when a piece is anchored in:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Home and property decisions</li>
            <li>Cleaning, maintenance, and repair</li>
            <li>Hiring trades and service businesses</li>
            <li>Quotes, scopes, and service standards</li>
            <li>DIY versus hire decisions</li>
            <li>Property expectations and inspections</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Value &amp; Trade-offs</h2>
          <p class="doc-meta">The cost-thinking lens</p>
          <p>The dominant question: <em>what does this choice cost over time?</em></p>
          <p>Use this desk for pieces about cheap versus expensive, false economy, rework, warranties, total ownership cost, premium versus good-enough, and the gap between sticker price and lifetime cost.</p>

          <h2>Internet Claims</h2>
          <p class="doc-meta">The claim-evaluation lens</p>
          <p>The dominant question: <em>what claim is being made, and what context is missing?</em></p>
          <p>Use this desk for pieces about reviews, rankings, "best of" lists, affiliate-driven advice, AI overconfidence, marketing language, influencer claims, and confident answers without consequences.</p>

          <h2>Work &amp; Standards</h2>
          <p class="doc-meta">The systems-thinking lens</p>
          <p>The dominant question: <em>what breaks when standards, ownership, or incentives are unclear?</em></p>
          <p>Use this desk for pieces about ambiguity, documentation, accountability, vague standards, misaligned incentives, and the operational failures that come from undefined "good."</p>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="paper-trail">
          <p class="doc-section__numeral">IV.</p>
          <h1>Paper Trail</h1>
          <p>Paper Trail shows the working behind a piece: how the conclusion was reached and how the piece was made. Every article carries one.</p>
          <p>It is built from three required fields, one optional field, and two extensions:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Method</strong> explains how the conclusion was reached.</li>
            <li><strong>Basis</strong> explains what the conclusion draws on.</li>
            <li><strong>Limits</strong> explains where the claim stops.</li>
            <li><strong>Time spent</strong> records the rough hours from concept to publication. Optional but recommended for substantive pieces.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Two extensions log changes over time: <strong>Updates</strong> record substantive editorial changes after publication, each dated; <strong>Retracted</strong> marks a piece formally withdrawn, with the URL kept live and a retraction notice in place of the body.</p>
          <p>The principle: Paper Trail should feel like method, not marketing. It says <em>here is how this conclusion was reached and how this piece was made</em>, not <em>here is why you should trust us</em>.</p>
          <p>If a Ledger piece cannot show its working, it does not belong here.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="independence">
          <p class="doc-section__numeral">V.</p>
          <h1>Editorial independence</h1>
          <p>The Ledger must stand on its own. It does not exist to justify a company, product, service, or side.</p>
          <p>Where a writer has a relevant connection to a subject, it is disclosed plainly and briefly — never as a selling point.</p>
          <p>If a piece exists mainly to make an outside business look good, it does not belong here.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="doc-section" id="corrections">
          <p class="doc-section__numeral">VI.</p>
          <h1>Corrections and retractions</h1>
          <p>The Ledger may get things wrong. When it does, the correction sits on the original piece — not buried, not quietly fixed, and never on a separate page that the original doesn't link to.</p>
          <p>Three kinds of change are handled three different ways.</p>

          <h2>Silent edits</h2>
          <p>Typos, grammar, broken links replaced with the current equivalent, formatting, and prose tightening that doesn't alter the argument. These are corrected without notice. They don't change what the piece is saying.</p>

          <h2>Logged updates</h2>
          <p>Substantive editorial changes — the conclusion shifts, a claim is removed or weakened, new evidence is added, the scope narrows or widens, the basis of the argument changes. These are recorded as a Paper Trail update at the bottom of the piece, with the date and a description of what changed. The article's modified date and byline update automatically. When in doubt, it's logged.</p>

          <h2>Retractions</h2>
          <p>When a piece is wrong enough that it should no longer stand, it is formally retracted — not deleted. The URL stays live. The body is replaced by a retraction notice naming the date and the reason. The original Paper Trail remains visible, so a reader can see how the now-withdrawn conclusion was reached. The piece is removed from the homepage, the desk index, and the RSS feed.</p>

          <p>Retraction is a recorded act, not a deletion. A reader arriving from an old link or citation lands on a real page that tells them the story.</p>
        </section>

      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  if ('IntersectionObserver' in window) {
    const sections = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.doc-section');
    const tocLinks = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLAnchorElement>('.doc-toc a');

    const setActive = (id: string) => {
      tocLinks.forEach((link) => {
        link.classList.toggle('is-active', link.getAttribute('href') === `#${id}`);
      });
    };

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      const visible = entries
        .filter((e) => e.isIntersecting)
        .map((e) => e.target as HTMLElement);
      if (visible.length === 0) return;
      visible.sort((a, b) => a.getBoundingClientRect().top - b.getBoundingClientRect().top);
      setActive(visible[0].id);
    }, { rootMargin: '-120px 0px -55% 0px', threshold: 0 });

    sections.forEach((section) => observer.observe(section));
  }
</script>

<style>
  .doc-title {
    padding: 88px 0 96px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .doc-title__eyebrow { margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .doc-title__title {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: clamp(56px, 11vw, 128px);
    line-height: 0.94;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .doc-title__title em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 300; }
  .doc-title__subtitle {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .doc { padding: 72px 0 96px; }
  .doc__inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
    gap: 96px;
    max-width: var(--max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--gutter);
  }

  .doc-toc {
    position: sticky;
    top: 32px;
    align-self: start;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 64px);
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding-right: 8px;
  }
  .doc-toc__label { margin-bottom: 22px; }
  .doc-toc ol {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .doc-toc a {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    transition: color 0.15s;
    padding-left: 12px;
    border-left: 1px solid transparent;
  }
  .doc-toc a:hover { color: var(--ink-2); }
  .doc-toc a.is-active {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 500;
    border-left-color: var(--ink);
  }
  .doc-toc__numeral {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 13px;
    min-width: 24px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .doc-toc a.is-active .doc-toc__numeral { color: var(--ink); }

  .doc-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .doc-section { margin-bottom: 96px; scroll-margin-top: 32px; }
  .doc-section:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .doc-section__numeral {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .doc-section h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(34px, 4.2vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .doc-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 48px 0 16px;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .doc-content h2 + .doc-meta {
    margin-top: -10px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .doc-meta {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .doc-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin: 36px 0 14px;
  }
  .doc-content p { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .doc-content strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }
  .doc-content em { font-style: italic; }

  .doc-content ul { margin: 0 0 24px; }
  .doc-content ul li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 26px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .doc-content ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .doc-content ol {
    counter-reset: doclist;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }
  .doc-content ol li {
    counter-increment: doclist;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .doc-content ol li::before {
    content: counter(doclist) ".";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .doc-content blockquote {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 4px 0 4px 28px;
    margin: 36px 0;
  }

  /* The definitive editorial test — pulled out of section II as a visual
     anchor so it reads as a rule, not as more paragraph copy. */
  .doc-filter {
    margin: 32px 0 40px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--paper-2);
  }
  .doc-filter__intro {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .doc-filter__question {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .doc-filter__question::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: -2px;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 22px;
  }
  .doc-filter__question em {
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .doc-filter__close {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 18px 0 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1000px) {
    .doc__inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 40px;
    }
    .doc-toc {
      position: static;
      max-height: none;
      overflow: visible;
      background: var(--paper-2);
      padding: 26px 28px 28px;
      border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    }
    .doc-content { max-width: none; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .doc-title { padding: 56px 0 64px; }
    .doc-title__eyebrow { margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .doc { padding: 56px 0 72px; }
    .doc-content { font-size: 17px; }
    .doc-content blockquote { font-size: 19px; padding-left: 22px; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .doc-title { padding: 44px 0 52px; }
  }
</style>
